Course:
    - name
    - capacity
    - waitlist
        - Queue ADT (Nodes, head, tail, size) (enqueue, dequeue, peek, isEmpty)
    - refactor to take EnrollmentRecord instead of student
    - enroll (student, date)
        - Ignore already enrolled students
        - If full, add to waitlist
        - Else, add EnrollmentRecord to the list of enrolled students
    - drop (student, replacement_date (optional))
        - If student is enrolled, remove them from the list of enrolled students
            - Use recursive binary search to find the student in the list of enrolled students 
                (when self.sorted_by is not "id")
        - If waitlist is not empty, enroll the next student in the waitlist with the replacement_date (or current date if not provided)
    - sort_enrolled(by=["name", "id", "date"], algorithm=["two", "sorts"])
        - Sort the list of enrolled students based on the specified attribute and algorithm
        - store by in self.sorted_by

EnrollmentRecord:
    - student (object)
    - self.date (datetime or "yyyy-mm-dd")

